    "Accessions with Hap-l exhibited greater salt tolerance and FtPK expression compared to that with Hap-2 (Fig. 4d, e), and the frequency of Hap-1 in high soil Electrical Conductivity (ECE) was higher than that in low soil ECE conditions (Additional file 2: Fig.",
    "S16), suggesting FtPK might play a positive role in Tartary buckwheat salt tolerance.",
